### Particle System
- Create 2000–3000 particles using THREE.BufferGeometry with Float32Array positions
- Distribute particles in a 3D volume: x/y spread wide (~2000 units), z depth between -500 and +500 units (creates the layered depth illusion)
- Particle material: THREE.PointsMaterial, size ~1.5–2.5, color white (#ffffff) or soft blue-white (#a8c8ff), transparent, opacity 0.7
- Vary particle sizes slightly using a size attribute array for depth realism

### Mouse Parallax (THE CORE EFFECT)
- Track mouse position globally via (mousemove) event on the host element
- Normalize mouse coords to -1..+1 range (divide by window width/height, multiply by 2, subtract 1)
- On each animation frame, smoothly lerp the camera position:
    camera.position.x += (mouseX * 80 - camera.position.x) * 0.05
    camera.position.y += (-mouseY * 80 - camera.position.y) * 0.05
  (the 0.05 is the easing factor — smooth follow, not instant snap)
- camera.lookAt(scene.position) every frame so it always points at center

### Depth layers illusion
- Split particles into 3 groups with different z-ranges and slightly different sizes/opacities:
    Layer 1 (foreground): z between -100 and 100, size 2.5, opacity 0.9
    Layer 2 (mid): z between -300 and 300, size 1.5, opacity 0.6
    Layer 3 (background): z between -500 and 500, size 0.8, opacity 0.3
- This creates genuine perceived depth on mouse move

### Subtle auto-rotation
- In the animation loop, slowly rotate the entire particle group:
    particles.rotation.y += 0.0003
    particles.rotation.x += 0.0001
- This gives ambient life when mouse is not moving

### Angular integration
- Use ngAfterViewInit() to initialize Three.js (DOM must be ready)
- Use ngOnDestroy() to cancel animation frame and dispose renderer (prevent memory leak)
- Handle window resize: update camera.aspect and renderer.setSize on (window:resize)
- Store animationFrameId as a class property for cleanup

### Code quality
- No external libraries other than Three.js
- Typed with TypeScript (import * as THREE from 'three')
- Self-contained in the component — no service needed
- Do NOT use any deprecated Three.js APIs (use BufferGeometry, not Geometry)

