### 4. Rules — do not break these

- animation-iteration-count: 1 (forwards) — plays once on hover, 
  does NOT loop infinitely (looping = cheap loading screen aesthetic)
- steps(1) timing — the clip-path snaps between positions, never 
  smoothly interpolates. This is what makes it feel like signal 
  fragmentation, not a CSS slideshow
- ::before is CYAN (#00ffff), ::after is RED/MAGENTA (#ff003c) — 
  these are the chromatic aberration colors. Do not change to 
  brand colors; the contrast against white base text is the effect
- Base text (.glitch-text itself) never moves — only the ghost 
  layers shift. This maintains readability throughout
- No JS animation loop, no requestAnimationFrame — mousemove 
  sets one CSS custom property and stops. That's it.

